+# Instrumentation Plan for Etcd Raft Snapshot Scenario
+
+This document outlines the modifications required for `state_trace.go` to support trace validation of the Snapshot scenario (`data/workloads/etcdraft/scenarios/snapshot/spec/Traceetcdraft.tla`).
+
+## 1. Trace Message Enrichment (Progress State)
+
+The `traceSendMessage` function needs to be updated to include full Progress state details when sending `MsgApp` and `MsgSnap` (mapped to `SendAppendEntriesRequest`).
+
+**Target Properties:**
+*   `state`: Current Progress state string (`StateProbe`, `StateReplicate`, `StateSnapshot`).
+*   `match`: `pr.Match` index.
+*   `next`: `pr.Next` index.
+*   `paused`: `pr.MsgAppFlowPaused` (boolean). Note: Spec models `MsgAppFlowPaused` explicitly.
+*   `inflights_count`: `pr.Inflights.Count()`.
+*   `pending_snapshot`: `pr.PendingSnapshot` (only relevant in `StateSnapshot`).
+
+**Implementation:**
+Retrieve `tracker.Progress` for the destination node (`m.To`). If it exists, populate the properties map.
+
+## 2. MsgSnap Content Correction
+
+The `makeTracingMessage` function currently maps `MsgSnap` properties incorrectly for our validation logic.
+
+**Current:**
+*   `Entries` = Snapshot Index
+*   `Index` = 0
+*   `LogTerm` = 0
+
+**Target:**
+*   `Index` = Snapshot Index (`m.Snapshot.Metadata.Index`)
+*   `LogTerm` = Snapshot Term (`m.Snapshot.Metadata.Term`)
+*   `EntryLength` = 0 (Empty entries list)
+
+This aligns with `Traceetcdraft.tla` expectations where `msg.index` is used as the snapshot index.
+
+## 3. Files to Modify
+
+*   `data/workloads/etcdraft/scenarios/snapshot/raft/state_trace.go`
+
+## 4. Verification
+
+After instrumentation, generated traces should contain `MsgSnap` events with correct `index` and `SendAppendEntriesRequest` events with detailed `prop` fields reflecting the internal Progress state machine.
